\begin_layout Standard
The objectives of this study are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
General Objective:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Evaluate the pore size distribution of Barra Velha Fm.
 Rocks from Mercury Injection Porosimetry (MIP) dataset.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Specific Objectives:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Conduct a detailed analysis of the porosity of the Barra Velha Formation,
 identifying specific characteristics that influence fluid retention.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Utilize the MIP technique to classify the pores found in the formation into
 micropores, mesopores, and macropores, providing a detailed categorization
 of the porous structure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Employ the Washburn Model as a specific tool to describe the dynamics of
 mercury intrusion into fine pores, contributing to the understanding of
 the relationship between pore diameter and applied pressure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Explore physics and mathematics issues associated with the problem, aiming
 to solve specific aspects related to the porosity of the Barra Velha Formation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Synthesize the obtained results to provide insights that may influence future
 strategies for oil exploration and production in the Santos Basin, especially
 in the region of the Barra Velha Formation.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
